content:
Automatically route work items directly to an agent using Direct-to-Agent routing.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud

To route all work items, except voice calls, enable Enable Skills-Based and Direct-to-Agent Routing in Omni-Channel Settings under Setup.

Follow the steps to create an Omni-Channel Flow.
Drag the Route Work action onto the canvas.
Give the action a label and an API Name.
Under Set Input Values | Record ID, select the recordId variable you created.
Under Route To, select Agent.
Select Agent—Specify the agent to route the work item to.
Use Variable—Use a variable to find the appropriate agent.
To assign work to only the preferred agent when they become available:
Click Required Agent.
Specify the Routing Configuration to use for routing parameters.

When a specific agent is required, Push Time-Out in the routing configuration settings or Allow Agents to Decline Work Requests are ignored.
title: Direct-to-Agent Routing in Service Cloud
